Over the course of a week I compared the Lumia 800, iPhone, and Galaxy Nexus. The following are my opinions of each which I hope will be useful to other people thinking about buying a new smartphone;
Size
I&rsquo;m going to say straight off that the Galaxy Nexus is too big to become my daily &lsquo;phone. I thought it would be when the specs started floating around, and, having had it a while now and travelled a bit with it, I still think it&rsquo;s true.

During my morning check of Twitter I came across this tweet from Google;
&ldquo;Introducing the #Google Chrome OS http://bit.ly/N1rNZ&rdquo;
Which started to raise some concerns. It had widely been predicted that we&rsquo;d see Android making it&rsquo;s way onto netbooks in the near future, but with this one announcement that idea has taken a huge knock backwards.
The reason is simple; Androids design is primarily focused on touch screen devices, Chrome OS is focused on netbooks, and netbooks rarely (if ever) have a touch screen.
